com.stormpath.sdk.authc

Interface AuthenticationResultVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuthenticationResultVisitorAdapter

    public interface AuthenticationResultVisitor
    A Visitor design pattern interface that allows one to react to different types of authentication results, particularly those reflecting successfully authenticated API requests (e.g. using ApiKeys.
    Since:
    1.0.RC
    See Also:
    ApiKey, ApiAuthenticationResult, OauthAuthenticationResult, AccessTokenResult

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void visit(AccessTokenResult result)
      Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated using the OAuth 2 protocol and the HTTP response must return a new OAuth 2 Access Token to the caller.
      void visit(ApiAuthenticationResult result)
      Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated with an ApiKey, usually as a result of HTTP Basic Authentication.
      void visit(AuthenticationResult result)
      Allows handling of a successful (usually username/password)-based authentication attempt.
      void visit(OauthAuthenticationResult result)
      Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated using the OAuth 2 protocol.

    • Method Detail

      • visit

        void visit(AuthenticationResult result)
        Allows handling of a successful (usually username/password)-based authentication attempt.
        Parameters:
        result - the AuthenticationResult instance reflecting a successful username/password authentication attempt.

      • visit

        void visit(ApiAuthenticationResult result)
        Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated with an ApiKey, usually as a result of HTTP Basic Authentication.
        Parameters:
        result - the ApiAuthenticationResult representing the successful API authentication attempt.

      • visit

        void visit(OauthAuthenticationResult result)
        Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated using the OAuth 2 protocol.
        Parameters:
        result - the OauthAuthenticationResult representing the successful OAuth-based API authentication attempt.

      • visit

        void visit(AccessTokenResult result)
        Invoked when an API request has been successfully authenticated using the OAuth 2 protocol and the HTTP response must return a new OAuth 2 Access Token to the caller. This almost always occurs as a result of handling a request to the application's OAuth 2 Access Token endpoint, for example, /oauth2/token.
        Parameters:
        result - the AccessTokenResult representing the successful OAuth-based API authentication attempt that must respond with an OAuth 2 Access Token response.
